programme.desc: Robson joins up with Sheli McCoy, AKA Gladiator Sabre, to explore her home area of Fife. A paddleboard tour of the coast is followed by a farm stay overnight. The morning sees them embark on a road trip to Anstruther, where they take a boat trip to the nature reserve of the Isle of May. Famous for its bird life, fauna and flora, the pair attempt to capture the scene with landscape artist Liz Myhill

programme.title: Call the Midwife
programme.desc: A new medical technique threatens to change the face of obstetrics forever, whilst a potential rabies outbreak has Poplar in a state of fear. Cyril meets Rosalind's parents

programme.title: Waiting for the Out
programme.desc: Haunted by memories of his absent father, Dan pushes his mother for answers she won't give. When Keith presents a lead, Dan spirals into obsession, straining family ties as he unravels at a dinner party. With Phil Daniels and Samantha Spiro

programme.title: The Traitors
programme.desc: The penultimate day in the castle commences with a mission offering a unique opportunity to the faithful. However, with time running out to build the prize pot, it seems possible that they might buckle under the pressure. As the players take their seats at the round table, the stakes have never been higher for the faithful to banish a traitor. Presented by Claudia Winkleman

programme.title: This Is BBC Two
programme.desc: Preview of upcoming programmes from BBC Two

programme.title: The Travelling Auctioneers: Treasure Dump for Dream Tickets
programme.sub-title: Treasure Dump for Dream Tickets Season 5, Episode 14
programme.desc: Shopaholic Johnny recently downsized from a four-bedroom house to a one-bedroom flat. Not only is his new home bursting at the seams, but so are his two storage containers, which are costing him over 1,000 a year. Izzie Balmer and Robin Johnson help him realise his dreams - not just saving on storage fees, but also to help fund the purchase of a vintage 1970s Chopper bike and VIP concert tickets for partner Donna

programme.title: Escape to the Country: East Sussex
programme.desc: Alistair Appleton helps a retired couple from the Surrey town of Epsom and their five sausage dogs find a home with space for larger rescue animals. Among the property contenders is a remarkable 400-year-old farmhouse bursting with original features and countryside character. Alistair's journey also takes him to meet a young edible flower farmer whose vibrant crops are as good for wildlife as they are for the plate

programme.title: Digging for Britain: A Mysterious Bone Box and Admiral Nelson's Favourite Ship
programme.sub-title: A Mysterious Bone Box and Admiral Nelson's Favourite Ship
programme.desc: Featuring an ft slipway in the New Forest where Admiral Nelson's favourite ship was built, an Anglo-Saxon cemetery where a host of well-preserved and rare objects have been found, and finds from Trinity College, Oxford. Plus, a late Roman cemetery that features an intricate bone box and part of a Roman bone flute, and a tangle of delicate Iron Age objects that have to be carefully micro-excavated in Kent

programme.title: BBC News: 23/01/2026
programme.desc: The latest national and international stories as they break

programme.title: Political Thinking with Nick Robinson: David Lammy
programme.desc: The journalist talks to the Deputy Prime Minister and Justice Secretary

programme.title: Live International Bowls: 23/01/2026
programme.desc: Live coverage from Potters Resorts at Hopton-on-Sea, Norfolk, featuring the second and third open singles quarter-finals. There were two all-English last-eight contests last year, with Robert Paxton and Mark Dawes overcoming Les Gillett and Paul Hartley respectively

programme.title: Flog It!: Sheffield 15
programme.desc: Paul Martin and the team value antiques in Sheffield, where experts Thomas Plant and James Lewis have their work cut out for them. A set of watercolours of the city appeals to Thomas, while James finds a Victorian automaton that causes a stir at auction. Plus, Paul takes time out to explore the story of the Great Exhibition of 1851

programme.title: Richard Osman's House of Games: Week 13 - Friday
programme.desc: Nadia Jae, Tamzin Outhwaite, Nigel Planer and Steen Raskopoulos test their skills in the final round of challenges on double points Friday

programme.title: Robson Green's Weekend Escapes: Matheson Green
programme.desc: Robson and his uncle Matheson discover the Hepple Estate on their doorstep in Northumberland, and wildlife artist Clare Brownlow shows them how to paint using pheasant feathers. The pair take a guided walk and learn how to track wildlife. Uncle and nephew end their short break by joining a pair of performers who teach circus skills

programme.title: Winterwatch
programme.desc: Chris Packham, Michaela Strachan and Iolo Williams spend a final evening at Mount Stewart, celebrating the best of the winter season. From memorable moments in that area to standout films from across the UK, they celebrate the resilience and beauty shown by wildlife during these cold winter weeks

programme.title: Monty Don's Rhineland Gardens
programme.desc: Monty travels beside the busy thoroughfare of one of Europe's most important rivers, the Rhine, through Germany. He follows the river past major cities, dramatic landscapes, and romantic castles and valleys, before reaching the flatter, industrial heartland of the country. Monty discovers an extraordinary range of gardens along the way - including a park created from disused factories

programme.title: Mystery Road: Origin
programme.desc: Jay's brother is blamed for a shooting, then another child vanishes, so the detective turns to extreme methods. Drama, starring Mark Coles Smith and Tuuli Narkle

programme.title: Natural World: Jungle Animal Hospital (Short)
programme.desc: The work of staff at a jungle animal hospital in Guatemala, where a dedicated team nurse their exotic patients back to health and prepare them for their return to the wild

programme.title: QI: Willy Nilly
programme.desc: Sandi Toksvig goes willy-nilly through the letter W as she and Alan Davies are joined by Josh Widdicombe, Catherine Bohart and Russell Kane

programme.title: Newsnight: 23/01/2026
programme.desc: Analysis of the day's events with Matt Chorley

programme.title: Weather: 23/01/2026
programme.desc: The latest forecast

programme.title: The Eternal Daughter
programme.desc: A middle-aged film maker and her elderly mother return to the old home of a relative, now an isolated hotel in the North Wales countryside, where the mother spent much of her life. Unable to make a start in preparing her new film, mother and daughter confront long-buried secrets. Drama, starring Tilda Swinton

programme.title: Panorama: Maxed Out: The Credit Card Trap - Panorama
programme.sub-title: Maxed Out: The Credit Card Trap - Panorama
programme.desc: Reporter Iona Bain investigates the hidden dangers of easy credit, from soaring interest rates and minimum payments, to lenders pushing higher limits and interest-free deal. With personal stories and expert insight, the programme asks if regulators are doing enough to protect the millions of people forced to rely on credit cards to make ends meet

programme.title: Lucy Worsley's Victorian Murder Club
programme.desc: The historian reveals that the trail had gone cold until a fifth dismembered corpse was discovered 12 years after the last murder. On June 8, 1902, two men spotted a bundle in Salamanca Place, Lambeth, containing the dismembered body of a woman and, for the first time, the woman's head. This new murder could contain a fresh lead, and the hunt for a Victorian serial killer ends with a convincing prime suspect

programme.title: Winterwatch
programme.desc: Chris Packham, Michaela Strachan and Iolo Williams broadcast from the Mount Stewart estate on the shores of Strangford Lough. The team slow down and discover the quiet wonders of winter, from wading birds gathering along the lough to the hardy woodland residents thriving among ancient trees. Featuring expert insight, intimate encounters and those first magical moments of the season

programme.title: Robson Green's Weekend Escapes: Jo Joyner
programme.desc: Robson takes fellow actor Jo Joyner horse riding near the small town of Wooler as he introduces her to his beloved Northumberland. The Cheviots provide a stunning backdrop at the riding centre at Kimmerton - where Jo gets back in the saddle for the first time in years. With her love of riding renewed, Robson takes Jo to Heatherslaw Mill for an outdoor cookery lesson to make soda bread

programme.title: Global Eye: 12/01/2026
programme.desc: BBC World Service cyber correspondent Joe Tidy is in Silicon Valley, California, to look at the impact of artificial intelligence and explore the next frontier of it

programme.desc: The cheese delivery race is on as Mojo and the Racer Top try to deliver food faster than Filo. But the competition gets too hot when an explosive souffle is on the table

programme.title: Big Lizard: The Day We Met Ammon
programme.sub-title: The Day We Met Ammon Season 1, Episode 4
programme.desc: Dad drops an essential gizmo in a hard-to-reach place. Big Lizard takes him and Cosima on an underwater adventure to meet Ammon, the tentacled solution to their problem

programme.title: Super Happy Magic Forest: The Over-Eager Eagle
programme.desc: Twinkle is unhappy with how easy questing has become since Cral joined the heroes, offending the eagle just when they need him the most

programme.title: Grizzy and the Lemmings: Jungle Rhythm
programme.desc: The Lemmings organise a dance contest, and the first prize is a jar of Yummy

programme.title: Grizzy and the Lemmings: The Grizming
programme.desc: An earthquake releases a strange creature preserved in a resin ball who turns out to be an ancestor of the Lemmings

programme.title: Stage Stars: Halloween
programme.desc: With Halloween approaching, the Year 7s go in search of the school ghost, while the Anything Goes cast try not to get spooked by the thought of opening night for their show

programme.title: Bro's in Control: Queasy Spa
programme.desc: Max and Harvey host the Queasy Spa quiz, where the Bros face some nauseating treatments. And can they pilot their own water jet packs in the Ultimate Memory Test?

programme.title: Cooking Buddies: Taye Fried Chicken
programme.desc: Buddy gets creative with street artist Taye and cooks a homemade crispy chicken fakeaway

programme.sub-title: Gladiators Takeover: Sporting Superstars Season 1, Episode 1
programme.desc: Sporting Superstars

programme.title: Newsround: 24/01/2026
programme.desc: Current affairs reports aimed at a younger audience

programme.title: Robson Green's Weekend Escapes: Chris Kamara
programme.desc: The actor is joined by football pundit Chris Kamara for a trip to North York Moors National Park. They catch up over high tea on a steam train before overnighting in a glamping pod at Yorkshire Burrows with views of the Howardian and Hambleton hills. The next day sees Robson and Chris go fossil-hunting at Saltwick Bay before they learn about traditional beekeeping using straw skeps

programme.title: Natural World: Heligan: Secrets of the Lost Garden
programme.sub-title: Heligan: Secrets of the Lost Garden Season 30, Episode 3
programme.desc: The secret lives of the wildlife in the popular Cornish tourist attraction, set against the background of the gardening year. Charlie Hamilton James shoots footage highlighting a variety of creatures inhabiting the estate, including foxes at play in the pleasure gardens after the visitors have left, toads mating and the badgers that enter the tea rooms at night. Narrated by Philippa Forrester

programme.title: Monty Don's Rhineland Gardens
programme.desc: Monty travels beside the busy thoroughfare of one of Europe's most important rivers, the Rhine, through Germany. He follows the river past major cities, dramatic landscapes, and romantic castles and valleys, before reaching the flatter, industrial heartland of the country. Monty discovers an extraordinary range of gardens along the way - including a park created from disused factories

programme.title: Homes Under the Hammer: Digging It
programme.desc: Jacqui Joseph is impressed that a first-floor flat in Aldershot, Hampshire comes with its own back garden, while Dion Dublin can see the money-making potential in a large house in Wallasey, the Wirral and a woman swaps hairdressing for house development in Great Yarmouth, Norfolk

programme.title: Bargain Hunt: Southwell 3
programme.desc: Eric Knowles hosts from Southwell Racecourse in Nottinghamshire. Experts Gary Pe and David Harper help the reds and blues decide which three items to spend their 300 on that they hope will make a profit at the auction in Lincoln. Eric also pays a visit to the Lincoln Vintage Vehicle Society to learn about the old craft of coachbuilding.

programme.title: Live International Bowls: 24/01/2026
programme.desc: Live coverage from Potters Resorts at Hopton-on-Sea, Norfolk, featuring the open singles semi-finals. Robert Paxton was victorious over David Gourlay in the first semi-final 12 months ago, and that was followed by Jason Banks defeating Mark Dawes in the second last-four encounter

programme.title: Flog It!: Hartlepool 32
programme.desc: Antiques and collectibles experts David Barby and Philip Serrell visit Hartlepool, Co Durham, where they provide bidders at auction with advice in their search for valuable trinkets that include a Biba dress and a treacle glazed ceramic lion. Presenter Paul Martin finds out about the German bombardment of Heugh Battery in December 1914

programme.title: Natural World
programme.desc: Documentary following the experiments carried out in America by Professor Con Slobodchikoff, who has recorded and analysed the phonetic patterns used by prairie dogs to communicate with each other. After spending 30 years studying the creatures, he thinks he has discovered a language second only to human speech in its complexity, which they utter to make other members of their community aware of impending danger from predators. Narrated by Rob Brydon

programme.title: The Magnificent Seven
programme.desc: Oppressed Mexican villagers cross the border into America looking to buy guns to defend their homes and crops from bandits. Instead they encounter an enigmatic loner who persuades them to hire a band of gunslingers to teach the villagers how to fight before the marauders return. Western, with Yul Brynner, Steve McQueen, Charles Bronson, Robert Vaughn, James Coburn and Eli Wallach

programme.title: Dolly Parton at the BBC
programme.desc: A selection of archive appearances by the country superstar on the BBC, including performances of Jolene, 9 to 5, Islands in the Stream and Here You Come Again. This collection showcases the enduring songwriting talents and sense of humour that first made Dolly's name back in the 1970s

programme.title: Dolly Parton: Here I Am
programme.desc: A profile of the American country star, charting the extraordinary life and music of the singer and songwriter. The documentary takes the audience on a musical journey through some of her greatest songs, including The Bridge, I Will Always Love You, and 9 to 5, and there is footage of Dolly celebrating the 50th anniversary of her first performance at the Grand Ole Opry. The film also features access to the singer herself, as well as collaborators from throughout her career

programme.title: Glastonbury 2014
programme.desc: The country singer's complete set on the Pyramid Stage at Worthy Farm in the now-traditional legends spot on Sunday afternoon, featuring Jolene, Coat of Many Colours, 9 to 5, Islands in the Stream and I Will Always Love You
